content.description: A superb route up a black varnished face.  Wanders past 11 bolts on excellent, thin patina crimpers and a couple improbable crux sequences to anchor.
content.location: Located downstream on the West Wall, past Stick It, just inside Shady Grove.  Just left of the Dark Star offwidth.

content.description: Start up the left side of the blunted arete.  The crux is a series of balancy moves between bolts 2 & 4.  Then over to the right side of the arete to a rest. Fun, airy moves on great patina edges up a steep, black face lead to the chains.
content.location: Located on the West side, about 3/4 of the way down-stream, on The Beach.  Vanilla Voodoo is the left-most (up-stream) of the 3 bolted aretes in a row.

content.description: A few moves up to the slanting rail, then a big move up and left, then up progressively easier ground to the anchor.
content.location: Located downstream on the West Wall in Shady Grove.  Just right of Slim Shady & left of Slap My Fro.

content.description: Gentle overhang to a leftward crux traverse at the very top.  Water/raft start.
content.location: Located well up the corridor.  Begins on a dark varnished face with nice pockets, followed by a  roof about thirty feet up.

content.description: Up and over a bulge to a good rest, followed by a very thin, technical finish.  Crux involves a deadpoint to a mono pocket.
content.location: In the corridor south of Throw Down the Gauntlet.  Raft/water start.

content.description: Follow thinning crack in corner to a bulgy crux up high, then up and right to chains.  The direct finish (up then right instead of right then up) is solid 10+ish.
content.protection: Lots of thin cams & nuts up to a #2 Camalot.
content.location: Downstream on West Wall in Shady Grove.  Thin crack in corner just right of The Winsloner & Darkstar.

content.description: Awesome clean crack in a corner that starts hands and gradually widens to fists (offwidth for small hands?)up high.  An excellent pitch!  Much of the climb is wide hands & cups for me, so those with small hands may find themselves doing lots of fist jams.
content.protection: In Camalot sizes I suggest 1 #1, 2 #2, 3-5 #3, plus a #4 Friend for the last bit.  YMMV.
content.location: Obvious beautiful corner crack downstream a bit on the West Wall, the next corner past Bro Job, and just before Shady Grove.

climbs.name: Sh'ash Nizhitl (The Bear that is Brown)

content.description: Beautiful brown patina face with small edges and great moves.
content.location: Right of Anti-Venom and left of American Beauty.

content.description: Scramble up to a small ledge about 10' high, just above the point where one wades through the water when walking downstream from Shady Grove.  Climb up a left-facing corner (funky gear), then up & left to another, larger corner.  Ascend this to the chains.
content.protection: Gear to #2 camalot, nuts, runners, & 3 bolts.
content.location: Located on the West side, just downstream from Hot Chocolate & Shady Grove.

content.description: From a sandy scoop delicately clip the first bolt before crimping and underclinging pockets.  Obtain a short rest by stemming in or near two scoops before a bout of patina pinching.  Run it out on easier, low-angle terrain before making a final move to the chains.
content.location: Located directly across from the rappel, 'The Sandstoner' is the leftmost of four delicate face routes.  These routes are left of 'Has Bro' and ascend the mushroom-like boulders.  'The Sandstoner' is on the West Wall.

content.description: Bouldery, with a chuck at the end.
Tricky start to nice pockets on well-featured face.  Water/raft start.
content.location: In the narrow corridor.

content.description: Being one of the more popular "hard" routes in the canyon, Picture Me is the one usually equipped with hanging draws. The route starts off with a great climbing on crimpy pinches, side pulls, and pockets, then transitions into the obvious stem where you can recharge your tendons. A couple hard cruxes follow.
content.location: One route to the left of Winsloner.

content.description: Beautiful varnished overhang with a blind deadpoint to a shallow pocket at the very top.  Swallows sometimes reside in the starting pockets.  Water/raft start.
Climbs bolted face just right of Lemongello to chains.
content.location: Located downstream on West Wall, just past Lemongello.

content.description: A decent route that climbs much better than it looks.  Traverse right & up to the 1st bolt, then interesting moves up past some nice rests.  Then up a steep bit to the chains.
content.location: Located on the West side.  It is the first sport route down-stream from the big hang-out boulder next to Has Bro.

content.description: From the anchor of Valley Girls, climb up and right to a hand crack in the obvious dihedral to the ledge. Take the right crack of the two cracks to another small ledge. If you have a #3 and #4 left, keep going. Otherwise stop your pitch here and anchor with 2 .75s and a nut; you'll then do a short second pitch.
content.protection: A couple of micro-cams, a double set .5 to #2, single #3 and #4, and medium to large nuts.  A second #3 and #4 will allow you to do this in one pitch instead of two.
content.location: Starts at the top of the route Valley Girls.  To descend, walk to and rap King Snake.   It's questionable whether or not you can rap King Snake with one 60m.  We swung over to the ledge left of King Snake where there is a middway anchor.

content.description: Start up crack then up & right past bolts through overhang.
content.protection: 1 each #1 Camalot & blue (or green?) alien, 3 bolts, chains.
content.location: Downstream of Shady Grove on West Wall, starts in crack below & just left of overhang.

content.description: Long route with all kinds of strange moves.  Water/raft start.
content.location: Twenty feet right of Perfection Project.

climbs.name: Kingsnake
climbs.fa: Jim Haisley and Scott Baxter, circa 1984

content.description: This is a long pitch with lots of hands, the pro is varied since the crack constricts often.  The rock quality is good as Red Rocks, nearing Wingate.  I think the belayer should be at the highest ledge to reduce rope drag but with runners and a runout, could be belayed from the ground.
content.location: As you rap into WW, this is the long corner just upstream on the west wall.

content.description: Work up the nice corner past adequate but un-inspiring pro to the roof.  Jam over the roof and up a beautiful splitter crack to the anchor.
content.protection: Thin to a #3 Camalot, nuts, and maybe an extra thin hand to hand piece or 2.  Bolts & chains at anchor.
content.location: Located dowwnstream on the West Wall in Shady Grove.  The obvious corner that leads to a roof.

content.description: Absolutely great, fingery route right across from the descent. Cool crimps, pockets, sidepulls and slopers take you to the chains. Climbs featured stone to the left of the arête line Has Bro.
content.location: Left of Has Bro.

content.description: An excellent route up a rounded arete.  Start just left of arete and climb past bolts to a move up & right near a roof crack.  Some people skip the last bolt on the arete.
content.location: On the West Wall across from the rappel gully, just before the big boulder.

climbs.name: The Hanging Judge
climbs.fa: Tim Coats and Tim Toula (circa 1984), FFA John Steiger and Ray Ringle

content.description:
This is an absolutely fantastic line consisting of sustained finger locking, lay-backing and precise foot work along a slightly overhanging wall, and a few rest points.

 The route starts on a ledge about 40 feet from the river. Getting there is kind of a sketchy 5.9. It is recommended to do this as an 'approach' short pitch. From there, it's 100 more feet to the bolted anchors.
content.protection: A good assortment of finger size cams (BD's from .3 to .75)... I recommend AT LEAST triples of each plus a few small microcams and nuts.
content.location: Directly across the river from the bottom of the rap line into the canyon.

content.description: Short and steep line on the right side of the wall above the "lunch rock". Very long moves.
content.location: On the West Wall, just right of Has Bro (11d) and Real Big Kung Fu (14a).

content.description: Starts same as Crack and Shatter, but arcs left to the spectacular, wavy arete.  Progressively harder climbing to a huge crux dyno.
content.location: A few feet right of Stick It.

content.description: The arete left of Stick it, starts on the left side of the arete, follows three bolts to an easy section, switches to the right side and stays there most of the rest of the way.  Multiple hard sections with the crux around the 5th bolt.  I've heard a range of ratings, and the crux is slabby, so consider the grade an estimate.  No idea who has the FA, but an excellent route to repeat.
content.location: Between The Brotheerhood and Stick It.

content.description: A nice face climb just right of an arete.  Start just right of Blackzilla in a grassy area.  Follow bolts to a crux up high, then continue up a few moves to the chains.  Also one can traverse left from the anchor to TR Blackzilla.
content.location: Located way downstream, past the scoop routes, on the left (West) side of the canyon, just up-stream from the 3 prominent bolted aretes, & just right of Blackzilla.

content.description: A tricky but well protected beginning crux involving scoop stemming, pocket pulling, and crimp grabbing sequence gives way to a hard 5.11 sequence on the patinated face of the climb. Traverse left to the shared anchors with Sandstoner.
content.location: The boltline immediately right and downstream of Sanstoner

content.description:
Obvious thin crossing crack/grooves.   My recollection is it was more about face climbing than fingers.  Climb it as a left to right system ? 

  Don't remember much.  I think it was a one pitch climb with some thin moves in an area lacking some pro ?  Bit of a challenging lead? 

  If someone has repeated this, fill in the details
content.protection: Two bolts off the deck, tips (blue tcu) to thin hands (bd #1) + finger sized nut. Doubles in .5 and .75 if you want the extra security!Edit: The two fixed pins have been replaced with bolts. Details in comments below.
content.location: In between Black Douglas and Kingsnake.   Should be recognizable due to a fixed pin,   I think near the X where the two thin cracks cross.   Shares anchor with Black Douglas.

content.description: Climbs obvious 'lightning bolt' offwidth in between the Winsloner & Valley Girl.  Start in a nice handcrack that quickly gets wide.  OW past a couple nice rests to the intermediate anchors on the right just after a short chimney section, which allow one to rap/TR with a single 70m rope.  Or just continue to top & use 2 ropes.  A nice line.
content.protection: 1 #2, 1 #3, 3-4 #4, & 2 #5 camalots.  Add a few more cams and a #6 if you want to feel extra secure.  Bolted rap anchor at 110', or continue to top.
content.location: Located downstream on the West Wall, just inside Shady Grove.

content.description: Gentle overhang with nice varnished edges, one of which is pretty thin!      Water/raft start.
content.location: Short distance upstream from The Black Douglas.  There's a big, obvious undercling at the start.

content.description: Back-to-back boulder problems on bullet rock followed by delicate climbing to the top. Route name largely attributable to Winslow prison inmate who demolished his cell window with two successive punches.
content.location: Left of Caligula.

content.description: Tall varnished face.  70m rope and about 20 draws required.  Belayer should knot the end of the rope.  Beware: deep pocket about 3 bolts from the top sometimes occupied by a bat.  Water/raft start.
content.location: Clean, verticalish wall well up the corridor.

content.description: A significant variation featuring endurance crimping for four bolts in place of Caligula's redpoint boulder problem crux
content.protection: 4 quickdraws for the bolts after splitting from Caligula
content.location: Start up Caligula.  Instead of clipping the fourth permadraw, clip up and left then head out onto the blunt arete, following crimps all the way to the top.

content.description: Thin technical climbing.
content.protection: 8 bolts to 2 bolt anchor, best to clip the first bolt of Picture Me and then the 2nd bolt of Caligula skipping the first bolt
content.location: Left of Picture Me Rollin'. Shares the last 2 bolts

climbs.name: The Brotherhood
climbs.fa: David Bloom, Doug Lafarge, Rich Ludwig

content.description: Fun, less than vertical start to a rest below a bulge with a seam. Negotiate the challenging bulge and veer Lt, and then Rt on varnished face above. Finally, a steep and exciting fisnish up another seam takes you to the anchor. Stemming lt into corner is off.
content.location: West wall. A bit Lt of obvious lt facing corner "Stick it"

content.description: Great route up thin patina edges.  Follow 7 bolts up to bolted anchor.
content.location: Just a bit downstream on the West Wall, just before the obvious splitter corner of Stick It.

content.description: A fun climb.  Start up face & crack past 1 or 2 placements, then up mostly overhanging jugs to anchor.
content.protection: 1 or 2 pieces (small-ish to hand-size), 3 or 4 bolts, and chains
content.location: On West Wall, downstream of Shady Grove, 2 climbs to the right of Lemongello.

content.description: A hard (for me) and sustained line with a few cruxy sections. Start in a grassy area just left of Ebonics. Climb face past 2 bolts to a short blank section below a small roof. Climb up to the roof (hard), then up & right at the roof (harder), then up and left, then through a final thin section (also very hard) to the anchors
content.location: Located way downstream, past the scoop routes, on the left (West) side of the canyon in a grassy area, just up-stream from the 3 prominent bolted aretes, & just left of Ebonics.

content.description: A featured & varnished corner.  Follow the featured crack up the corner until it is possible to traverse left to Bro Job's anchors.  At the base is often a mini-swamp, so take care when pulling the rope.
content.protection: Gear to 4".  Anchor is Mussy hooks at the top of Bro Job.
content.location: Located on the West side, just downstream from the rap in gully.  Black Juju is the obvious dark corner just right of Bro Job.  It is located about 30' up-stream from the super-obvious corner of Stick It.

content.description: A few sketchy moves up & left to the 1st bolt, then up steep patina edges past 2 cruxes with a nice rest in between.  Towards the top the holds get bigger.
content.location: On the West side, just UP-stream from the rap in gully, in the Kingsnake/Hanging Judge alcove.  Located on the far left side of the steep, dark wall that forms the left side of the corner on Kingsnake.

content.description: A beautiful stunning line with excellent rock and great movement. A cool low crux from the first to the second bolt gets you to a great rest on a small ledge. Now suss your way through amazing thin patina edges and crimp holds that seem to magically appear just when you need them. The climbing eases off when you can grab the left side of the arete again.
content.location: the middle of the three bolted aretes. One bolted route downstream of Vanilla Voodoo

content.description:
A physical route up stems, wide cracks, & a squeeze chimney.  A more accurate rating might be 5.9+++. 

  Start by stemming up a wide crack in a right-facing corner.  Continue up past a weird squeeze slot thing to fun, steep moves past horizontals to the anchor up & right.
content.protection: Cams to at least a #4 camalot, larger nuts, & slings.  Fixed anchor.  An extra #2 &/or #3 camalot may prove helpful.
content.location: Located way downstream on the East side in the area known as The Beach.  Starts in a right-facing corner, just right of the 3 aretes.  Watch out for poison ivy.

content.description: use the offwidth crack on the right to gain the first bolt and some good pockets. From here move up a bit to clip the second bolt and out left engage the low crux to the third. Very fun black petina crimp and edge climbing with another high crux. After the high crux the route eases off
content.location: The rightmost route of the three bolted aretes.

content.description:
A very tall pretty line with great features and fun movement. It is definitely worth doing once. The crux is a bouldery sequence getting past the first bulge but then the route mellows out significantly on black patina all the way to the top. The route would be great if it were more sustained and did not go over a huge bulge, creating rope drag, and obstructing the view of the belayer.  

  note: I would not recommend top roping this climb as the pendulum swing at the crux will cause the lip of the bulge to saw the rope
content.location: one bolted route downstream of barracuda, which is the rightmost of the three bolted aretes

content.description: A solid route that climbs much better than it looks.  Start up a thin, featured crack with occasionally funky pro to better jams & gear to a rest.  Then up & left (1st crux) to some nice finger locks to a nice ledge.  Then face climbing up the right-facing corner past bolts to the 2nd crux, an improbable traverse right & up to easier ground.
content.protection: Bolts.  Single rack to #3, nuts & slings.  some small Tricams would work well also.  For extra security bring an extra #2 camalot.
content.location: Located on the West side, at the far down-stream end of Shady Grove, just down-stream from Hot Chocolate.

content.description: The leftmost of the three “Bro” routes. Thin, technical face climbing.

A great climb up great rock.  Start right of the arete, just left of Hot Chocolate.  Climb up and left to arete, then up past many bolts to top.  Technically the crux is up high, but there are several cruxy sections throughout the climb.  This one is full-value!
content.location: Located downstream on the West Wall, on the prominant arete in the middle of Shady Grove.  Just left of Hot Chocolate and 3 climbs to the right of Darkstar.

content.description: West side of the canyon, afternoon shade.
